{"type":"message","id":"4c5b823e","parentId":"1fd9eea5","timestamp":"2026-04-21T07:34:43.228Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try a different approach. Since multi-search-engine-simple doesn't exist as an npm package, and web search is difficult to get working well with Chinese content, let me try using the agent-reach skill's Exa search via mcporter, or try other approaches.\n\nActually, wait - I should check if there are any MCP servers available in this environment that could provide search capabilities. Let me also try installing beeos which was mentioned in the npm search results.\n\nBut actually, looking at this more carefully, the user asked me to use \"multi-search-engine-simple\" specifically. This doesn't exist on npm. \n\nI'll explore a few alternatives: trying to install beeos-search or beeos from npm or Homebrew, checking what MCP servers might already be configured, attempting to reach a Bing API, and leveraging whatever knowledge I have about 私域运营 jobs to save into memory.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4dd6f54377f6436db800447e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try beeos tools\nbeeos --help 2>&1 | head -20\necho \"---\"\nwhich beeos 2>/dev/null; brew list beeos 2>/dev/null","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-dashscope-aliyuncs-com","model":"qwen3.6-flash","usage":{"input":42352,"output":446,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42798,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776756864475,"responseId":"chatcmpl-8add71fd-cc79-9c81-8e8d-eb85b4baabcd"}}
